                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/91.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 31.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department is in receipt of your despatch No.
                    14, of the 28th of November last, reporting the status of the proposed
                    construction of the Panama-David Railway.</p>
                <p>A copy of the despatch has been sent to the Secretary of War, for his
                    information.</p>
                <p>The matter of the construction of the Panamá-David Railway is now being
                    considered by the War Department in conjunction with congressional action
                    looking to the operation and maintenance of the Panama Canal.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>(For <signed>Mr. Knox</signed>:) <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
